tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild hypoglycemia and low HbA1c, with elevated creatinine suggesting impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals significant proteinuria, glycosuria, ketonuria, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), but no evidence of infection. These findings are consistent with possible diabetic nephropathy and renal impairment, despite low blood glucose. Further clinical correlation and nephrology evaluation are recommended.
